{"type":null,"faqId":26432,"title":"Troubleshooting Touchscreen Failures","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333\">Troubleshooting Touch screen Failures</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">1. If the touch screen failure occurs when\nyour phone is charging, a possible reason is that you are not using the\noriginal charger. In this case, the charger's output voltage is unstable, which\nwill cause touch screen failures. Use the original charger where possible. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">2. The screen protective film may make the touch\nscreen fail to respond properly. Remove the screen protective film if any, and\ntry again. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">3.The touch screen failure may be caused by\nelectrostatic. Press the power button twice to release the electrostatic. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">4. The issue may be caused by the system\nsoftware. Back up important data and restore your phone to its factory\nsettings. If the problem persists, check for software updates and update your\nphone. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">5. If the screen failures are resulted from\nhardware fault or occur after your root your phone, please contact an\nauthorized Huawei service center. </span></p>\n<br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":1,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"831","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433165663000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":336,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Troubleshooting Touchscreen Failures","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}